response.name: Tokyo-to
response.description: The sprawling metropolis where most of the Jet Set Radio events take place. Divided into three major areas: Shibuya-Cho, Kogane-Cho, and Benten-Cho.

sub_locations.name: Shibuya-Cho
sub_locations.description: A district known for its bustling streets and the famous Scramble Crossing. It's a popular hangout for the GG's.

sub_locations.name: Kogane-Cho
sub_locations.description: An old-school district with a lot of traditional Japanese architecture. The player can grind on power lines and rooftops.

sub_locations.name: Benten-Cho
sub_locations.description: A nightlife district filled with neon signs and an urban setting. Home to the Love Shockers gang.

response.name: Grind Square
response.description: Often considered the heart of Tokyo-to, it features high rises and plenty of rails to grind on.

response.name: Bantam Street
response.description: Notorious for its steep hills and tight corners. Bantam Street will test the player's control and precision.

response.name: 99th Street
response.description: An iconic location filled with bright murals and graffiti. It serves as a battleground between rival gangs.

response.name: Sky-Dinosaurian Square
response.description: This is where the players can skate on top of skyscrapers and perform death-defying stunts.

response.name: The Sewers
response.description: Underground area perfect for pulling off tricks against a gritty backdrop. It's a maze of pipes and tunnels.

response.name: Fortified Residential Zone
response.description: A high-security area patrolled by the Rokkaku Police Force. Challenges players with its restricted access and abundance of security measures.

response.name: Rokkaku-Dai Heights
response.description: The corporate stronghold of the Rokkaku Group. Offers a mix of corporate buildings and urban terrain to explore.
